The paper deals with the problem of finding the optimal center of a star graph to minimize its dilation, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper involve computational methods such as sorting and binary search (cs.NA) and probabilistic analysis (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which is related to the theory of computational complexity (cs.DM).
